g?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"CC&Rs (Covenants, Conditions, and Restrictions) are the legal rules governing your property. They dictate everything from paint colors to parking rules to pet policies. I always tell buyers to read the full CC&Rs before closing. What is in that document will affect your daily life."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How do I get a copy of the CC&Rs before buying a home?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Your REALTOR or the listing agent can request them from the HOA or management company. In Florida, sellers are required to provide HOA documents to buyers, and you have a 3-day right to cancel after receiving them for resale properties. Do not waive this review period."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can the HOA tell me what color to paint my house?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Most HOAs have an approved color palette for exterior paint. You typically need to submit a request to the Architectural Review Committee before making any exterior changes. This includes paint, landscaping, fencing, and even mailbox modifications."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Are there breed restrictions for dogs in Florida HOAs?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Many HOAs have breed restrictions, commonly prohibiting pit bulls, Rottweilers, German Shepherds, Dobermans, and other breeds deemed aggressive. Some also have weight limits (e.g., no dogs over 40 pounds). If you have a specific breed, check the CC&Rs carefully before making an offer."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can an HOA limit how many pets I have?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Many HOAs limit the number of pets per household, commonly to 2 or 3. Some restrict pets to dogs and cats only. Exotic pets, chickens, and livestock are almost always prohibited. Pet rules are one of the most common things buyers overlook in CC&Rs."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What are common HOA violations in Florida?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answe